Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Context Engineer* role with *Adobe*. I bring over three years of professional experience designing and deploying LLM-powered systems in production, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my engineering roles, I have built production-grade context pipelines and LLM systems that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed and implemented context pipelines that assemble few-shot examples, chain-of-thought scaffolding, and structured prompt formatting to deliver accurate, safe LLM responses across 1,000+ platform endpoints — requiring deep command of tokenization, prompt formatting, and context window constraints. I also architected memory mechanisms for conversational state management, including summarization, pruning, and context compression strategies, and optimized token limits and prompt routing to reduce end-to-end latency by 60% and LLM API costs by 50% across production workloads. I established and documented context engineering best practices adopted across the platform team — directly mirroring the standards-setting responsibilities central to this role. Prior to Sperse, at Qualitest, I built an internal support chatbot using LangChain and retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) with a PostgreSQL vector store, structuring enterprise knowledge for natural-language queries and reducing ticket resolution time by 20% — giving me hands-on experience with the cross-functional knowledge structuring Adobe's Digital Employee Experience team requires.

My research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in model development and technical communication. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I applied PyTorch, Hugging Face, and vLLM for model training, fine-tuning, and inference, with a focus on tokenization and context window optimization for efficient production serving. I also led workshops on LangChain, LangGraph, and AI Agents for 50+ students — translating complex NLP and LLM concepts for non-technical audiences, which mirrors the cross-functional collaboration and knowledge-sharing Adobe values in this role.

I have always been passionate about empowering people through technology and raising the bar on what AI systems can do for human productivity — two values at the heart of Adobe's mission to change the world through digital experiences. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

